{
  "texts": [
    "It is clear that the original ambiguous instruction has been broken up into two sequential subtasks that match well the metaAgent's capabilities (see Fig. 3a).",
    "Afterwards, through consultation with the grounding expert, the metaAgent assigns to each subtask an action function and associated devices from FunctionLibrary and DeviceLibrary, respectively.",
    "For subtask-1, the chosen action function and device are 'user_localization' and the 2.4 GHz SPM, respectively.",
    "Similarly, 'breathing_detection' and the 5.5 GHz SPM are chosen for subtask-2.",
    "Note that the metaAgent automatically chooses a set of 20 random coding patterns for the action function 'user_localization' while it chooses the focusing coding pattern for 'breath-ing_detection' in order to suppress unwanted clutter by boosting the signal-to-noise ratio."
  ]
}